This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Symbolic Computation (cs.SC) as it deals with the use of cylindrical algebraic decomposition (CAD) which is a well-known technique in symbolic computation. It also involves the use of equational constraints (ECs) which are commonly used in symbolic computation. 

It could also belong to the sub-category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) as it deals with logical implications of formulas and equations. 

Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) is another likely sub-category as CAD is used in automated reasoning and theorem proving, which are important areas of AI. 

Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) is also a possible sub-category as CAD involves the manipulation of data structures such as cells and polynomials. 

Finally, Computer Graphics (cs.CG) is a less likely sub-category as CAD is used in geometric modeling and visualization, which are important areas of computer graphics.
